[[File:Theresa May foreign trips.png|thumb|300px|World map highlighting the 31 countries visited by Theresa May during her premiership, as of {{monthyear}}]]
This is a '''list of international prime ministerial trips made by Theresa May''', the current [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom]]. As of {{monthyear}}, [[Theresa May]] has made 60 trips to 32 countries since her [[Premiership of Theresa May|premiership]] began on 13 July 2016.

The number of visits per country: 
* One visit to [[Argentina]], [[Bahrain]], [[Bulgaria]], [[Estonia]], [[India]], [[Iraq]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]], [[Japan]], [[Kenya]], [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]], [[Malta]], [[Nigeria]], [[Norway]], [[Slovakia]], [[South Africa]], [[Spain]] and [[Turkey]]
* Two visits to [[Austria]], [[Canada]], [[China]], [[Denmark]], [[Poland]], [[Jordan]], [[Netherlands]], [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Sweden]] and [[Switzerland]]
* Four visits to [[Italy]] and the [[United States]]
* Seven visits to [[France]] and [[Germany]]
* Nineteen visits to [[Belgium]]

