| {{flag|Saudi Arabia}}
| [[Riyadh]]
| {{sort|2017-04-03|4–5 April}}
| May visited [[Saudi Arabia]], in order to hold talks about counter terrorism, security, the Middle East crisis as well as future trade links. May met with the Saudi Minister of Energy to discuss energy policy, as well as investment opportunities on the London Stock Exchange. May also met with the Saudi Interior Minister to discuss terrorism and security. On 5 April, May met with [[King Salman]] of Saudi Arabia to discuss security and trade. May was honoured by King Salman with the [[Order of King Abdulaziz]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/pm-meetings-in-saudi-arabia-4-april-2017|title=PM meetings in Saudi Arabia: 4 April 2017 - GOV.UK|website=www.gov.uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/pm-meeting-with-king-salman-of-saudi-arabia-5-april-2017|title=PM meeting with King Salman of Saudi Arabia: 5 April 2017 - GOV.UK|website=www.gov.uk}}</ref>
