| {{flagu|Saudi Arabia}}
| Riyadh
| {{sort|2017-11-28|28–29 November}}
| May visited Saudi Arabia to strengthen trade links between the two nations (Saudi Arabia being the United Kingdom's biggest trading partner in the Middle East) for the UK post-Brexit. She met with Crown Prince [[Mohammad bin Salman]] to discuss the [[2016–17 Yemen cholera outbreak|humanitarian crisis in Yemen]] and to discuss Saudi Arabia's [[Qatar–Saudi Arabia proxy conflict|diplomatic crisis with Qatar]].<ref name="Saudi Jordan Second Visit">{{cite web|last=Merrick|first=Rob|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/theresa-may-middle-east-post-brexit-links-trade-saudi-arabia-jordan-yemen-un-uk-a8080796.html|title=Theresa May arrives in Middle East to strengthen post-Brexit links with other trading partners|work=The Independent|date=28 November 2017|accessdate=29 November 2017}}</ref>
