| {{flagu|Belgium}}
| Brussels
| {{sort|2017-12-08|8 December}}
| May again travels to Brussels, where European Commission President Juncker announces a "breakthrough" Brexit deal had been reached following negotiations.<ref>https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-42277040</ref> 
The deal outlines agreements on issues such as: protecting the rights of Union citizens in the UK and UK citizens in the Union; the framework for addressing the unique circumstances of Northern Ireland: and the financial settlements<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ec.europa.eu/commission/sites/beta-political/files/joint_report.pdf|title=Joint report from the negotiators of the European Union and the United Kingdom Government on progress during phase 1 of negotiations under Article 50 TEU on the United Kingdom's orderly withdrawal from the European Union|last=|first=|date=8 December 2017|website=European Commission|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=8 December 2017}}</ref>
